-- India Sets Benchmark Price for Gold Import Duty
-- B y   T h o m a s   K u t t y   A b r a h a m
-- 2012-01-23T05:51:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/india-sets-benchmark-price-for-gold-import-duty-correct-.html
(Corrects to benchmark price in story first published on
Jan. 18.)  India , the world’s biggest gold
consumer, set the benchmark price for setting tax on imports of
the precious metal at $526 per 10 grams, according to an e-
mailed statement from the nation’s Central Board of Excise &
Customs.  The benchmark price for imports of silver was set at $953 a
kilogram, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Thomas Kutty Abraham at 
 tabraham4@bloomberg.net  